'''Floryshe''' ("To Flourish") is an English term from at least the mid 1300s used in the brief English sword text, MS 39564, c. mid-1400s, to refer to the brandishing of a weapon with large showy movements during practice or prior to play or fight. The modern used to mean a practice routine of guard changes, cuts, thrusts, and slices with appropriate footwork.